The paper deals with privacy preservation and verifiability in online auctions, which are common topics in computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of encryption schemes and protocols also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). The optimization of computation and communication overheads may relate to game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
